  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "MPEG PS uses pack+PES structure. Start codes always begin with 0x000001. After the pack header (0x000001BA), PES packets follow with stream IDs: 0xE0-0xEF video, 0xC0-0xDF audio. MPEG-1 system streams may start directly with 0x000001B3 (video sequence header) with no pack wrapper.",
    "suggestedInspections": [
      "Identify start code at offset 0: 0xBA=MPEG-2 PS pack, 0xB3=raw video, 0xB9=sequence end",
      "For MPEG-2 PS: parse SCR from pack header to determine stream timing base",
      "Walk PES packets after each pack: check stream_id for video (0xE0) vs audio (0xC0)",
      "For elementary streams (0x000001B3): parse sequence header for width, height, aspect ratio",
      "Detect MPEG-1 vs MPEG-2 by SCR byte upper bits: '00'=MPEG-1, '01'=MPEG-2",
      "Scan for private stream 1 (0xBD) PES packets to find AC-3 or DTS audio tracks"
    ]
  },
